SIMPLE: remitter
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Remitter
<hw>Re*mit"ter</hw> <pr>(-t?r)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One
who remits.</def> <specif>Specifically:</specif> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>One
who pardons.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>One who makes remittance.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Law)</fld> <def>The sending or placing back of a
person to a title or right he had before; the restitution of one who
obtains possession of property under a defective title, to his rights
under some valid title by virtue of which he might legally have entered
into possession only by suit.</def> <rj><au>Bouvier.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Remittitur</ent>⟦br⟧
\'d8
